==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paranymph
<hw>Par"a*nymph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>paranymphus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <grk>para`</grk> beside, near + <?/ a
bride: cf. F. <ets>paranymphe</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr.
Antiq.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A friend of the bridegroom who went with
him in his chariot to fetch home the bride.</def> <au>Milton.</au>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The bridesmaid who conducted the bride to the
bridegroom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>An ally; a supporter or
abettor.</def> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paranymphal</ent>⟦br⟧
